EsrCost - Class in optimizer
The EsrCost class represents a row in the ESR cost table, which maps the capacity of an ESR to its capital cost.
simple example:
* sample row:(20,30,100,10)
* cost of a 25 litre tank = 100 + 10*(25-20) = Rs 150

Constructs an EsrCost object with the specified parameters.
EsrCostStruct - Class in structs
The EsrCostStruct class represents the cost information of an ESR (Elevated Storage Reservoir).
An instance of this class represents one row of the ESR cost table, which maps the capacity of an ESR to its capital cost.
